This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) as it discusses the use of Wiktionary as a resource for NLP tasks and describes an open-source Wiktionary parser. It may also belong to Information Retrieval (cs.IR) as it involves extracting information from a large database of text. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of machine learning techniques, which could place it in the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper's focus on parsing and extracting information from a large dataset could also place it in the sub-category of Deep Learning (cs.DL).
